Dashboard integrates sales, profit, cost, and customer data into one interactive platform.

Provides clear visibility into KPIs: $29.36M sales, $12M profit, 60K customers, $17.27M costs.

Reveals seasonal demand peaks, especially in Q3, guiding marketing and inventory planning.

Highlights top products (Mountain-200, Road-150) as revenue drivers.

Identifies underperforming items and growth potential in accessories and clothing.

Shows US and Australia as dominant markets, with scope to expand in Canada and France.

Customer insights emphasize mid-to-high income buyers and untapped female segment.

Pinpoints inefficiencies in production costs, suggesting optimization opportunities.

Recommends loyalty programs for high-value customers to boost retention.

Positions dashboard as a strategic tool for efficiency, diversification, and long-term growth.
